---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.jsx";
---

<MainLayout>
  <Navbar client:load />

  <main class="min-h-screen px-6 pb-28 pt-36">

    <!-- ── § About / Background ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <p class="mb-6 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § About / Background
      </p>

      <h1 class="mb-12 max-w-4xl font-light leading-tight text-slate-100">
        <span class="block text-4xl md:text-5xl">Building practical systems.</span>
        <span class="block text-4xl md:text-5xl text-[#A5B5A3]">
          Growing into backend-focused full-stack engineering.
        </span>
      </h1>

      <div class="grid gap-14 lg:grid-cols-[0.85fr_1.15fr]">

        <!-- Current Focus card -->
        <aside class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
            § Current Focus
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm font-light leading-relaxed text-[#D8E0DD]">
            <li>→ Building backend systems that go beyond the tutorial</li>
            <li>→ Authentication, protected routes, and real database persistence</li>
            <li>→ Full-stack apps with accessible, low-pressure interfaces</li>
            <li>→ Testing, deployment, and documentation as first-class concerns</li>
            <li>→ Learning to explain engineering concepts in Japanese</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <!-- About prose -->
        <div class="flex max-w-3xl flex-col gap-10 text-base font-light leading-8 text-[#D8E0DD]">
          <p>
            I build full-stack and backend systems with React, TypeScript,
            FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Docker, and GitHub Actions.
          </p>

          <p>
            My focus is turning beginner projects into realistic engineering
            systems — the kind with real authentication, persistent databases,
            protected routes, clean documentation, and deployment workflows
            that actually hold up.
          </p>

          <p>
            I'm drawn to backend architecture, accessibility, and products
            that solve real problems without overwhelming the people using
            them. That interest led to Bloom — an accessible routine and
            focus app built around low-pressure user experience and calm,
            inclusive design.
          </p>

          <p>
            I use every project as an engineering lab: a place to practise
            debugging, architecture decisions, Git workflow, testing, and
            explaining technical choices clearly — not just to make things
            work, but to understand why they work.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── § Direction ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-40 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mb-24 border-t border-white/20"></div>

      <p class="mb-12 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § Direction
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Backend Engineering
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            Building APIs that hold up — authentication, database
            persistence, structured routes, validation, testing,
            and deployment with FastAPI and PostgreSQL.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Full&#8209;Stack Systems
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            Connecting frontend to backend with React and TypeScript —
            protected routes, API integration, accessible interfaces,
            and user flows that work end to end.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Technical Communication
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            Writing clearly about technical decisions — README files,
            architecture notes, debugging recaps, and documentation
            that makes projects readable beyond the code itself.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── § Background ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-40 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mb-24 border-t border-white/20"></div>

      <p class="mb-12 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § Background
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Education
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            MSc Computer Science — currently in progress.
            Building engineering fundamentals alongside
            practical project work.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Experience
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            ADAS Operations at Tesla, EMEA. Operational
            systems experience that shaped how I think about
            reliability, process, and attention to detail.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Location
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            London and Edinburgh. Open to remote, hybrid,
            and international roles. Working toward
            technical communication in Japanese.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── § Building ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-40 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mb-24 border-t border-white/20"></div>

      <p class="mb-12 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § Building
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-6 text-sm font-light leading-relaxed text-[#D8E0DD]">

        <li class="flex flex-col gap-2 border-b border-white/10 pb-6">
          <span class="text-base font-normal text-slate-100">Bloom</span>
          <span>
            An accessible routine and focus app for neurodivergent users.
            React · FastAPI · PostgreSQL · JWT auth · v2.0.0 in progress.
          </span>
        </li>

        <li class="flex flex-col gap-2 border-b border-white/10 pb-6">
          <span class="text-base font-normal text-slate-100">
            AI HR Support Assistant
          </span>
          <span>
            Full-stack LLM-integrated support tool.
            React · TypeScript · FastAPI · PostgreSQL · Docker.
          </span>
        </li>

        <li class="flex flex-col gap-2 border-b border-white/10 pb-6 last:border-b-0 last:pb-0">
          <span class="text-base font-normal text-slate-100">
            JWT Authentication Dashboard
          </span>
          <span>
            Role-based access control with OAuth2 and JWT.
            FastAPI · React · TypeScript · Vercel · Render.
          </span>
        </li>

      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ── § Approach ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-40 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mb-24 border-t border-white/20"></div>

      <p class="mb-12 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § Approach
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm font-light leading-relaxed text-[#D8E0DD]">
        <li>→ Build things that work before making them clever</li>
        <li>→ Understand the error before reaching for the fix</li>
        <li>→ Write code as if someone else has to read it tomorrow</li>
        <li>→ Documentation is part of the work, not an afterthought</li>
        <li>→ Ship something small and real over something large and theoretical</li>
        <li>→ Build for real people, not ideal users</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ── § Writing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mx-auto mt-40 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mb-24 border-t border-white/20"></div>

      <p class="mb-12 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § Writing
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1fr]">

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Technical Log
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            Field notes from building production-style apps —
            bugs, decisions, fixes, and the reasoning behind them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start">
          <a
            href="/technical-log"
            class="inline-block border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-light text-[#D8E0DD] transition hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-slate-100"
          >
            Read the log →
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</MainLayout>